%N A394289 Decimal expansion of the asymptotic probability that the p-adic valuations of two positive integers selected independently at random are coprime for every prime p dividing both integers.
%C A394289 Equivalently, the asymptotic probability that the greatest common (1+e)-divisor of two positive integers selected independently at random is squarefree (see A049599 for the definition of a (1+e)-divisor).
%F A394289 Equals Product_{p prime} (1 - 1/p^2 + (1 - 1/p)^2 * Sum_{k>=1} mu(k)/(p^k-1)^2), where mu is the Moebius function.
%e A394289 0.958024304885093797499370832030193894313158894884929...
%o A394289 (PARI) c(m) = prodeulerrat((1-1/p^2) + (p-1)^2/p^2 * sum(k = 1, m, moebius(k)/(p^k-1)^2));
%o A394289 {my(c1 = 0, c2 = 1, m = 2); while(c2 != c1, c1 = c2; c2 = c(m); while(!issquarefree(m++), m++)); c2}
%Y A394289 Cf. A008683, A049599, A256936.
%K A394289 nonn,cons,changed
%O A394289 0,1
